'''''Fun Home''''' (subtitled ''A Family Tragicomic'') is a [[Graphic novel|graphic]] [[memoir]] by American writer [[Alison Bechdel]], author of the [[comic strip]] ''[[Dykes to Watch Out For]]''. It chronicles the author's childhood and youth in rural [[Pennsylvania]], USA, focusing on her complex relationship with her father. The book addresses themes of [[sexual orientation]], [[gender role]]s, [[suicide]], [[dysfunctional family]] life, and the role of [[literature]] in understanding oneself and one's family. Writing and illustrating ''Fun Home'' took seven years, in part because of Bechdel's laborious artistic process, which includes photographing herself in poses for each human figure.<ref name="tcj36">{{Cite journal
 | last = Emmert
 | first = Lynn
 | date = April 2007 
 | title= Life Drawing
